No, it's two separate processes.

35:56.280 --> 36:01.080
So you can generate spirit names by using tables of Hebrew letters,

36:03.320 --> 36:10.360
using a sigil to tell you which cell in the table you go to from which cell and on to which cell

36:11.160 --> 36:19.240
you spell out a name, or even the reverse process, you spell the name onto the table

36:19.240 --> 36:20.920
and that gives you the spirit sigil.

36:21.800 --> 36:26.040
Because the ingredients that you need for an evocation are the name of the spirit,

36:26.840 --> 36:33.000
the sigil of the spirit, and then you need to calculate what's the best time to call them,

36:34.680 --> 36:35.880
et cetera, et cetera.

36:36.520 --> 36:41.960
That's using tables to produce the name of spirits or to check the sigil or to reverse

36:41.960 --> 36:47.960
that, but it's not the whole process.

36:48.920 --> 36:52.680
Encrypting the message for the spirit is a separate process.

36:52.680 --> 36:58.600
So you know the spirit name, you call the spirit, you tell the spirit your message in

36:58.600 --> 37:04.920
whatever form, whatever language, whatever cryptographic form, and then he will convey

37:04.920 --> 37:14.280
that more or less accurately, and I can't swear always accurately, to the distant friend or

37:15.560 --> 37:21.960
who is similarly aware of this magical technique, and then he will say the necessary words,

37:22.680 --> 37:26.840
and more often than not, the message will come to him and dream.

37:27.240 --> 37:35.800
The trisimus says the spirit will whisper it in his ear, but my experience is that

37:35.800 --> 37:37.080
doesn't always happen.

37:37.080 --> 37:41.560
It's more likely to turn up in the dream on the following night.

37:42.120 --> 37:44.760
Reminds me, Dr. Skinner, of something you touched on before.

37:45.640 --> 37:52.200
There's a, I believe in the PGM, there's a spell that says that you can have a message

37:52.200 --> 37:59.320
and the deity will appear in someone else's dream as the God that they believe in,

37:59.320 --> 38:00.760
as opposed to what you believe in.

38:02.520 --> 38:04.440
That's a very sneaky piece of magic.

38:07.400 --> 38:13.640
I do know the method for inserting thoughts into other people's dreams in such a way that

38:13.640 --> 38:19.880
they will believe it's their own thought, because you wake up in the morning and not all the thoughts

38:19.880 --> 38:28.600
in your head do you immediately recognize, but a much more effective way is to have

38:29.320 --> 38:34.680
in that person's dream a figure who is their God appear to them and tell them,

38:35.240 --> 38:39.160
you must do this, you must do that, and then they can go, oh my God told you.

38:40.680 --> 38:44.760
If it's a Catholic, it may be a saint.

38:45.720 --> 38:52.600
If it's a pagan, then it may be a pagan God, but to incorporate that God into the

38:52.600 --> 38:56.120
delivery of the message makes it very highly effective.

38:57.240 --> 39:01.800
As well, Dr. Skinner, I think this next part touches on something that you brought up at

39:01.800 --> 39:06.600
the beginning of our chat and also something David Rankin talks about when he, in his

39:07.320 --> 39:12.920
Grimoire Encyclopedia, when he talks about the building of magical momentum or magical tension

39:12.920 --> 39:20.600
and you say, quote, that the mental effort involved in encoding the message to the spirit

39:21.160 --> 39:27.480
is part of the magical procedure, end quote. Can you share why is this so important, Dr. Skinner?

39:28.680 --> 39:33.960
Well, most people take a very casual attitude to magic. I'll just quickly

39:33.960 --> 39:39.160
rattle through the invocation and then I'll tell the spirit what I want. No, you have to use

39:39.160 --> 39:44.840
a lot of, I wouldn't say brain power, but a lot of intention.

39:47.320 --> 39:52.120
People will say that magic is mostly psychological. I definitely don't believe that,

39:52.760 --> 40:01.560
but I know that when you do it, it must be done with intention and carefully and precisely,

40:01.880 --> 40:06.520
which is why three of my books start with the word techniques of.

40:07.960 --> 40:17.560
Technique comes from a Greek word, which means a craft or a procedure. I like to think of

40:17.560 --> 40:25.080
magic as something that is done scientifically, but only scientifically in the sense of

40:25.960 --> 40:33.080
method. So you try something out, you record your results, you formulate series and that,

40:33.080 --> 40:37.880
and then you test the series. Well, it's not quite as complicated as that in magic,

40:37.880 --> 40:42.360
because a lot of the instructions are already available in the grimoires,

40:43.480 --> 40:51.560
and so you use them, but you use them carefully and with attention. Just as if you were driving or

40:51.560 --> 41:00.360
flying a rapid plane, you need attention and intention, otherwise you might come to a nasty,

41:00.360 --> 41:07.960
nasty sticky end. Yes, so you would consider Dr. Skinner this mental technique, this preparation

41:07.960 --> 41:13.480
of encoding the message as just as important as, say, gathering your materia magica, your wand,

41:13.480 --> 41:17.880
your sword, consecrating things. It sounds like it's that important to the technique.

41:18.440 --> 41:23.400
Yeah, yeah, and producing your ray of tools and people say to me, well, why do you need

41:23.400 --> 41:30.120
tools for magic? Why can't you just sit in your arm chair and think about it? That does not work,

41:32.360 --> 41:38.280
but at least it doesn't work for me. There may be people who can do that, but not anybody I

41:38.280 --> 41:46.600
immediately know. And you see the same thing in Chinese magic or even martial arts. I mean,

41:46.680 --> 41:53.240
there's a well-known story of a village which was being attacked by some raiders,

41:54.200 --> 42:06.120
and one of the team masters there tried to contract a samurai to teach them how to fight with

42:06.120 --> 42:12.840
swords and fight these people off who are destined to arrive in the next week or something. And of

42:12.840 --> 42:18.440
course, the master said, you've got to be kidding. I can't teach you what you need to know in a week.

42:19.000 --> 42:25.080
Tell me what you do know. And he said, well, I know how to do the tea ceremony. And I do that

42:25.080 --> 42:35.240
with a lot of attention. And I do that regularly. And I'm really a master of that. So the samurai

42:35.240 --> 42:42.120
simply taught him how to clean the sword and replace it in a scabbard and told him to apply

42:42.120 --> 42:49.960
the same degree of intention to that as he did to the tea ceremony. So when the raiders turned up,

42:51.320 --> 42:55.800
there was the team master pretending to be head of the village,

42:56.600 --> 43:04.040
and laid out in front of him was one or two pieces of equipment. And he cleaned them and

43:04.040 --> 43:08.760
presented them in the way that he would have done for the tea ceremony. And the raiders looked and

43:08.760 --> 43:14.680
they saw this guy treats his tools like this. He obviously knows what he's doing.

43:15.400 --> 43:24.600
We'll go and find an easier village to raid and they left. So the point of that slightly oblique

43:24.600 --> 43:32.360
story is that the weapons and they are called weapons of magical practice need to be treated

43:33.080 --> 43:40.680
great deal of respect and intention. And they need to be exercised and consecrated.

43:42.680 --> 43:49.400
And these actions then give them much more than psychological power, but it does give them

43:50.440 --> 43:56.520
power that then can work. And the spirits can appreciate that. They look at a magician who

43:56.520 --> 44:03.880
lays out his tools properly, leans them, wraps them in the right colored silk and so forth. And

44:03.880 --> 44:09.640
they figure, this guy knows what he's doing. We better not mess with him.

44:11.240 --> 44:18.360
People find it hard to understand when I explain it. But I think the Chinese team master

44:19.240 --> 44:23.000
is a good parallel. Absolutely. One of the ways I've phrased it is,

44:23.720 --> 44:27.480
based on everything that you've shared and Fraterashin Shasan and other guests is,

44:28.520 --> 44:34.280
instead of operating on the laws of physics, many grimoire interactions and evocatory procedures

44:34.280 --> 44:41.160
operate on the laws of meaning and intention and being able to meet them in a specific laid-down

44:41.640 --> 44:48.200
pre-mutually agreed upon terms and a specific ritualistic structure that gets results. I don't

44:48.200 --> 44:54.360
know if that's a fair way to think about it. And going back to previous conversation we had a few

44:54.360 --> 45:05.000
minutes ago, in the Greek magical papyri and in the old Egyptian temples, anybody who had just

45:05.000 --> 45:11.080
eaten garlic or fish was not allowed to come in and was certainly discouraged from doing any ritual

45:11.880 --> 45:18.280
or worship or ritual inside the temple because the spirits do have a great sense of smell.

45:19.480 --> 45:24.920
So the spirits can cotton on to what we're doing, that we're doing the right technique

45:25.800 --> 45:33.720
and that we are masters of what we are doing. And that instills a certain amount of fear and

45:33.720 --> 45:39.240
obedience. Dr. Skinner, in addition to those vital elements, one of the things that you mentioned

45:39.240 --> 45:45.400
that's necessary for the successful completion of an evocatory procedure in the grimoire tradition

45:45.400 --> 45:52.840
is the seal, the sigil of the spirit. And to that very point, the very few number of seals

45:52.840 --> 46:00.120
found in the Stegonographia match exactly to the seals found in the second book of the Lamegaten,

46:00.120 --> 46:07.160
namely the Theurgia Goetia. So can you share, Dr. Skinner, why doesn't the Stegonographia contain

46:07.160 --> 46:14.600
more of these seals? Right. So as I've already explained, to call the spirit, you need its seal

46:15.400 --> 46:20.360
so that it's not sufficient to have the Stegonographia. You've got the evocations,

46:20.360 --> 46:26.680
you've got the spirits' names, you've got the times, etc. But when Trasimius is writing that,

46:26.680 --> 46:33.080
he also composed the Theurgia Goetia, Don't Be Distracted by the Name,

46:34.040 --> 46:40.840
which I think is a later edition. And in that, he had the same spirits, but he had their seals.

46:41.400 --> 46:48.440
And he knew, being a sensible lad, that you should keep these two elements separate. However,

46:48.440 --> 46:52.200
if you're a practicing magician, then you need to bring these two elements together,

46:52.920 --> 46:58.280
and you use the seals in the Theurgia Goetia, which you've got the same spirit names as the

46:58.360 --> 47:04.760
invocations, etc. in the Stegonographia. So I suppose this is a little plug for,

47:05.720 --> 47:14.040
yes, if you're going to do this, you also need to buy Dr. Rudd's Goetia, because in there will be

47:14.040 --> 47:21.720
the seals that you need. I see that Alex is waving it around. Thank you very much. And that's another

47:21.800 --> 47:29.880
coincidence. It's part of my progress through the Grimoires to cover, hopefully, all the bases

47:31.000 --> 47:39.800
by the end of my time. I think historically, the Theurgia Goetia was made at the same time

